Creating graphs in R with ggplot2

Melissa Anderson

2024-07-23

Look! I made a graph

Notice how I put the code in a chunk and then made a graph. Pretty neat, eh?

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_line()

I can make a scatter plot. . .

gg_base <- ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors))
gg_base +
  geom_point()

Or, I can make a column plot.

gg_base +
  geom_col()

Finally, let’s wrap up with an area plot.

gg_base +
  geom_area()

gg_base +
  geom_point(
    aes(size = visitors,
        color = visitors),
    alpha = 0.5
  ) +
  theme_void()

gg_base +
  geom_line(linetype = "dotted") +
  theme_minimal() + 
  theme(panel.grid.minor=element_blank(), panel.grid.major=element_blank())

  labs(
    x = "Year",
    y = "Annual park visitors",
    title = "Channel Islands NP Visitation",
    subtitle = "(1963 - 2016)"
  )
## $x
